To add a custom repository type in Gradle, you need to follow these steps:

1. Create a new file in the root directory of your project called `build.gradle` (if it doesn't already exist). This file is the main build script for your project and contains all the configuration details.

2. Inside the `build.gradle` file, add the following code to define a new repository type:

```groovy
repositories {
    maven {
        url "https://your-custom-repository.com/"
        content {
            includeGroup "your.custom.group"
            includeArtifact "your.custom.artifact"
        }
    }
}
```

Replace "https://your-custom-repository.com/" with the URL of your custom repository, and "your.custom.group" and "your.custom.artifact" with the appropriate values for your custom group and artifact.

3. Save the file and synchronize the Gradle project.

Now you have added a new custom repository type in Gradle. This will allow you to access and use packages from your custom repository.

Note: If you need to authenticate with the repository, you can add authentication details inside the `maven` block like this:

```groovy
maven {
    url "https://your-custom-repository.com/"
    credentials {
        username "your-username"
        password "your-password"
    }
    content {
        includeGroup "your.custom.group"
        includeArtifact "your.custom.artifact"
    }
}
```
Replace "your-username" and "your-password" with your actual authentication details.

